The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 CAB wants Sourav back in Team India

A STAFF REPORTER 

Calcutta: The Cricket Association of Bengal (CAB) wants Sourav Ganguly back in the national side. 

The CAB working committee, following a meeting on Monday, decided to write a letter to the BCCI, requesting Souravs reinstatement. 

Sourav deserves a place in the (Indian) side, especially after the way he performed in Mohali against Punjab (in their Ranji Trophy opener). It shows hes fit and in fine nick, CAB president Jagmohan Dalmiya told mediapersons after the meeting. 

Sourav made 43 in the second innings on a difficult track with plenty of pace and bounce. 

According to CAB joint secretary Saradindu Pal, the committee also unanimously decided to write a letter the BCCI, requesting it to pave the way for Souravs return to Team India. 

The letter will be sent on Tuesday, he added. 




